Bolt

Target IP:

Scanning



There are three TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH, HTTP, and another HTTP.

Enumeration

Port 8000: HTTP


This is an interesting CMS application.



There are three possible usernames here: jake, admin, and bolt. Pressing the Message for IT Department button reveals the password boltadmin123 of the admin user bolt.


Scanning for directory and files was tough as it was incredibly slow. I had to research to find out where the admin panel is located. I finally found the admin panel at /bolt/login. After using the username and password, I gained access to the CMS application as shown above. The version of the application is also shown as 3.7.1.

Exploitation & Flag


I used the module exploit/unix/webapp/bolt_authenticated_rce to exploit the vulnerabililty. I used Metasploit as it contains a working exploit for this version. The options I set are shown above.


After deploying the exploit, I gained a root shell on the target machine.


There is only one flag on this target machine which is shown above.
